INSERT INTO `blog_article` VALUES (1,'DEFENSE CHIEF CONTRADICTS TRUMP ON IRAQ AND OIL','WORLD,JAMES MATTISDONALD, TRUMPIRAQ','The U.S. military is \"not in Iraq to seize anybody\'s oil\", Defense Secretary Jim Mattis said, distancing himself from remarks by President Donald Trump, as he held talks with Iraqi leaders on Monday.',NULL,'<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Mattis was the highest-ranking Trump administration official to visit Iraq since Trump irked Iraqis with a temporary ban on travel to the United States and for saying America should have seized Iraq&#39;s oil after toppling Saddam Hussein in 2003.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Trump told CIA staff in January: &quot;We should have kept the oil. But okay. Maybe you&#39;ll have another chance.&quot;</p><p class=\"trial-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-weight: 600; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 26px; line-height: 30px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; position: relative; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); white-space: normal; widows: 1;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsweek.com/trial\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-width: 0px; border-top-style: none; border-right-style: none; border-left-style: none; border-color: initial; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-decoration: none; color: black;\">Try Newsweek for only&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(255, 5, 0);\">$1.25 per week</span><span class=\"icon\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"></span></a></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Mattis, however, flatly ruled out any such intent. &quot;We&#39;re not in Iraq to seize anybody&#39;s oil,&quot; he told reporters traveling with him late on Sunday, ahead of his arrival.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">&quot;All of us in America have generally paid for our gas and oil all along and I&#39;m sure that we will continue to do so in the future,&quot; said Mattis, a retired Marine general who once led forces in Iraq.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\"><span class=\"figure embed\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px 0px 20px; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-align: center; display: block;\"><img width=\"961\" height=\"643\" class=\"mapping-embed\" src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20170221/1487626548106546.jpg\" alt=\"Jim Mattis\" title=\"\"/><span class=\"figcaption\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 10px 0px 37px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-align: left; color: rgb(24, 24, 24); position: relative; font-family: &#39;Source Sans Pro&#39;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; display: block;\"><span class=\"caption\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 10px 0px 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; display: block; font-weight: 600; font-size: 16px; line-height: 20px;\">U.S. Defense Secretary Jim Mattis addresses a news conference during a NATO defence ministers meeting at the Alliance headquarters in Brussels, Belgium, February 16, 2017. REUTERS/Francois Lenoir/File Photo</span><span class=\"credit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 10px 0px 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; display: block; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase;\">REUTERS/FRANCOIS LENOIR</span></span></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">His remarks are the latest sign of differences with Trump. Trump has acknowledged that Mattis disagrees with him about the usefulness of torture in interrogation and said he would defer to his defense secretary on the issue.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Mattis has been more critical than Trump of Russian President Vladimir Putin, and distanced himself from Trump&#39;s labeling of the media as &quot;the enemy of the American people&quot;, saying he had no problems with the press.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">A retired Marine general who led American troops in Iraq, Mattis has sought an exemption from Trump&#39;s travel ban for Iraqis who have served with U.S. troops, including translators.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">He said he had not seen a new executive order which the administration is considering. &quot;But I right now am assured that we will take steps to allow those who have fought alongside us, for example, to be allowed into the United States,&quot; Mattis said.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Mattis&#39; visit came a day after Iraqi Prime Minister Haideral-Abadi announced the start of a ground offensive on westernMosul, where Islamic State militants are under siege along with an estimated 650,000 civilians.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">It was unclear whether Trump&#39;s remarks on oil had come up during Mattis&#39; with Abadi, who has told Washington that Iraq&#39;s oil is the property of Iraqis.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Mattis also met Iraq&#39;s defense minister and top U.S. officials in Iraq.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">Will U.S. Forces Stay After Mosul?</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Influential Shi&#39;ite cleric Moqtada al-Sadr on Monday called on Iraq&#39;s government to order the withdrawal of U.S. and allied forces after the battle of Mosul is over.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">&quot;The Iraqi government has to demand that all occupying and so-called friendly forces leave Iraq in order to preserve the prestige and the sovereignty of the state,&quot; Sadr said.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Mattis declined to address Sadr&#39;s remarks directly, describing them as an internal political matter.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">But he said he was reassured after his talks in Baghdad that Iraq&#39;s leaders recognized the value of its relationship with the United States.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">&quot;I imagine we’ll be in this fight for a while and we’ll stand by each other,&quot; he said, repeatedly praising the resilience of Iraqi forces.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">The U.S. commander in Iraq, Army Lieutenant General StephenTownsend, has said he believes U.S.-backed forces will recapture both of Islamic State&#39;s major strongholds—Mosul and the city of Raqqa in Syria—within the next six months.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Trump is looking for a plan to accelerate the campaign against Islamic State, which could lead to an additional deployment of U.S. forces, who currently number less than 6,000 in Iraq and Syria.</p><p>Related Stories</p><ul style=\"list-style-type: none;\" class=\" list-paddingleft-2\"><li><p><a href=\"http://www.newsweek.com/russia-mattis-position-strength-pentagon-557418?utm_source=internal&utm_campaign=incontent&utm_medium=related1\" class=\"article-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-decoration: none;\">Russia Demands U.S. Explanation Of Mattis&#39;s Comments<span class=\"overlay article-overlay\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"></span></a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"http://www.newsweek.com/nato-spending-us-james-mattis-557206?utm_source=internal&utm_campaign=incontent&utm_medium=related2\" class=\"article-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-decoration: none;\">U.S. Threatens to &#39;Moderate&#39; Commitment To NATO<span class=\"overlay article-overlay\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"></span></a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"http://www.newsweek.com/iraqi-offensive-eliminate-isis-mosul-558431?utm_source=internal&utm_campaign=incontent&utm_medium=related3\" class=\"article-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-decoration: none;\">Iraqi Offensive Aims to Eliminate ISIS From Mosul<span class=\"overlay article-overlay\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin: 0px; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"></span></a></p></li></ul><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">The Pentagon may also look at increasing the number of attack helicopters and air strikes and bringing in more artillery, as well as granting greater authority to battlefield commanders fighting Islamic State.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">Townsend told a news conference in Baghdad he had been putting U.S. military advisers closer to front lines in Mosul than before, a move that would increase risk but bolster their ability to aid Iraqis, including by directing air strikes.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px none; list-style: none outside none; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; outline: none 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: rgb(60, 60, 60); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19.2px; line-height: 29.6832px; white-space: normal; widows: 1;\">&quot;We adjusted our posture during the east Mosul fight and we embedded advisers a bit further down into the formation,&quot; he said.</p><p><br/></p>',1487626575,'REUTERS',3,1),(2,'Your True Stories, in 100 Words',NULL,'Everybody has a story to share. What\'s yours? Tell us here for the chance to be published in Reader\'s Digest.','uploads/20170220163956720.jpg','<p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">A SOLDIER’S SUPRISE</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by&nbsp;Gail Litrenti-Benedetto, Park Ridge, Illinois</em></p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">It is spring of 1943 during World War II. Standing among hundreds of new soldiers at Camp Grant, in Illinois, my father, Sam, just 18 years old, waits as a truck slowly drives by. A full field pack is randomly tossed to each soldier. “How strange,” my father thinks, as he sees his last name, Litrenti, marked on each item in his pack. “How did they know it was me when they tossed the pack?” He was impressed! Beating all odds, my father was tossed a field pack from World War I—his own father’s.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;</p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">SMOKE SIGNALS</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by Dan Rolince, Golden, Colorado</em></p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">On a cool night lit only by the orange glow of fire, we rushed to my grandfather’s home as his decades-old barn burned to the ground. The firemen let us stand nearby as they pumped water from the creek a quarter mile away. We watched the barn go up in flames, which stirred memories of jumping off foot-wide wooden beams into the hay below. The real sadness came as my elderly grandfather, who did not get out of bed, quietly asked if his cows were safe. He hadn’t had dairy cows in a dozen years.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">A MOTHER’S WISDOM</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by&nbsp;Lori Armstrong, Kelseyville, California</em></p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">I have always worn my children’s birthstones around my neck. One morning, when I was late for work, my infant son Larry’s topaz birthstone fell from my gold chain. I frantically searched for it, whispering to myself, “I lost my Larry, but I will get him back.”</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">That day, Larry’s cardiologist called with test results from one of his first checkups. He would need emergency heart surgery. Happily, the operation was a success, and I whispered in Larry’s ear, “I thought I lost you, but I knew I’d get you back.”</p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\"><img class=\" wp-image-150454 size-medium\" src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20170221/1487626818922171.jpg\" alt=\"may 2016 true stories\" width=\"219\" height=\"300\"/><span class=\"credits-overlay\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both;\"><span class=\"image-credit\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; font-style: inherit; font-weight: normal; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 3px 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 136, 136); text-transform: uppercase; display: block;\">KAGAN MCLEOD FOR READER&#39;S DIGEST</span></span></span></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">THE GOOD DOCTOR&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by Danica Helfin, Tifton, Georgia</em></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Toto was a white dog with a small red tongue, and his stuffing was red as well. When his seams began to come apart beneath his knitted collar, it looked to my six-year-old eyes as though he were bleeding. That night, my father left for his shift in the emergency room with Toto wrapped in a blanket. The next day, Dad showed me the X-rays and Polaroid photographs of the<br/>surgery. Beneath the bandage on Toto’s neck was a clean row of stitches. I still have the injury report! I love you, Dad.</p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">A SMALL FORTUNE</span><br/><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by Ron Fleming, Fort Drum, New York</em></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">While walking across an open, grassy field, I became excited as my hand swooped toward the ground like an eagle attacking its prey. I picked up half of a $5 bill. I continued to walk around looking for the other half but thought to myself it would be impossible to find it on such a windy day. As I lifted my head, I spotted the other half of the bill tangled in crabgrass. Somehow, finding two halves of a ripped $5 bill felt better than working for a twenty.</p><p class=\"continues-below\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; color: rgb(136, 136, 136); text-align: center; text-transform: uppercase; width: 643.275px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">CONTENT CONTINUES BELOW AD</p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">SWEET SLEEP</span><br/><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by Suzanne Cifarelli, Albany, New York</em></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Don’t let her sleep in your bed.” That’s what I heard over and over after my daughter was born.<br/>So I didn’t, unless she was sick. Now my baby is almost six, and every night, after we read and sing songs and turn off the light, I lie down with her before she falls asleep. We whisper to each other, and I watch her eyelids start to flutter. I smell her hair and kiss her forehead. And I wish I had done this every night.</p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">MY MASTERPIECE&nbsp;</span><br/><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by Angela Bradley-Autrey, Deer Park, Washington<br/></em></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: -0.1pt;\">I was four, playing outside in the humid Kentucky air. I saw my grandfather’s truck and thought, Granddad shouldn’t have to drive such an ugly truck. Then I spied a gallon of paint. Idea! I got a brush and painted white polka dots all over the truck. I was on the roof finishing the job when he walked up, looking as if he were in a trance.<br/>“Angela, that’s the prettiest truck I’ve ever seen!” Sometimes I think adults don’t stop to see things through a child’s eyes. He could have crushed me. Instead, he lifted my little soul.</span></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">THE LONG LIFE OF ROOM 1108&nbsp;</span><br/><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by Laurie Olson, Dayton, Nevada<br/></em></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: -0.1pt;\">A long flight of weathered steps led to a hollow wooden door with rusty numbers beckoning us into room 1108. Inside, we barely noticed the lumpy bed, faded wood paneling, and thin, tacky carpet.<br/>We could see the seashore from our perch and easily wander down to feel the sand between our toes. We returned again and again until the burgeoning resort tore down our orange-shingled eyesore. Forty years later, my husband periodically sends me short e-mails that declare the time: 11:08. “I love you, too,” I write back.<br/></span></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">A Date With Fate&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br/><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.03125em;\">by Emily Page Hatch, Wilmington, North Carolina<br/></em></p><p class=\"Body-Txt-DROPCAPBASICS\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: -0.1pt;\">In a kitschy bar in Cambridge, he asked to sit at my table, though later he would insist that I made the first move. I was intrigued by his tattoos. He thought I went to Harvard. All we had in common was that we’d both almost stayed home. Friends had dragged us out on a frigid February evening. We still never agree on anything, except that it’s a darn good thing we sucked it up that snowy night. Our wild blue-eyed son always stops us in our tracks, reminding us that fate is just as fragile as our memory.</span></p><p><br/></p>',1487626821,'ADER\'S DIGEST EDITORS',1,3),(3,'This Faucet Will Change the Way You Think About Aging','sports, celebrity',NULL,'uploads/20170220164058913.jpg','<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">I ask my grandpa what it feels like to grow old. He ponders this question while we sit in his office overlooking the yard, the same yard I pulled weeds in when I was a boy.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">It is late in the afternoon, but Grandpa is wearing pajama bottoms, slippers, and a thick flannel shirt. His face is withered, his once taut flesh sagging loosely from his bones. A cup of black tea rests on the wooden desk in front of him. Grandpa drank coffee most of his life but switched to tea a few years back, when coffee became too hard on his stomach.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Grandpa’s mind brightens and dims like a beam of light under­neath a magnifying glass on a cloudy day. But on good days, on days like this one, there’s a break in the clouds and the sun shines through again.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">He gazes out the office window and looks at his yard, which has gone into a state of decline in recent years. Grandpa no longer possesses the energy to maintain its once magnificent splendor. Tree branches droop over the fishpond he built, the pond’s surface covered with a layer of green algae. Weeds sprout around the brick path weaving through the garden. An empty bird feeder dangles lifelessly from a tree limb.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Grandpa and I spent many hours during my summer vacations from elementary school working in the yard. We started in the afternoon when the sun was near its zenith. Grandpa would don an Oakland Fire Department baseball cap, faded blue jeans, and a white T-shirt. Back then, he was a tireless man with a burly body like a sailor.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">My main job was weed patrol, because Grandpa performed the glamorous work, excavating the rich California soil for a new addition to his ever-­expanding yard. He grew tomatoes on metal stakes and planted strawberries, lettuce, and radishes in the ground. And when they were ripe for picking, he’d bring them inside to Grandma’s kitchen so they could be prepared.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Grandpa was an artist. The yard and garden were his canvases, the flowers and plants his palette of paints. He was constantly bent over on all fours honing his art, the knees of his jeans stained brown.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">At the end of the day, in the early evening, the air would become crisp and cool. Before calling it quits, Grandpa and I would wash up and get a drink of water at the hose on the side of the house. Grandpa would give the T-handle on the spigot a turn or two. The limp hose would stiffen, and then he’d cup his hand underneath the hose, the water pooling tranquilly in his palm. He’d lift his hand to his mouth and drink, quenching his thirst with each sup.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">I tried imitating him but could never clench my fingers tight enough, and the water would slip through the slits of my fingers and dribble wastefully to the ground.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.875em; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 22.2222px; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But before going inside, we’d fill up the bird feeder next to the pond. I’d go to the garage and find the seed bag, a blend of sunflowers, cracked corn, and millet. We’d walk into the garden, sauntering along the brick path to where the bird feeder hung from the tree. Grandpa would remove the top of the feeder—a wooden ­rooftop—­and lift me by my armpits. Then I’d pour the seed into the feeder, my shoes dangling near his thighs.</p><p><br/></p>',1487626886,'su',0,2),(4,'This Faucet Will Change the Way You Think About Aging',NULL,NULL,'uploads/20170220164157455.jpg','<p style=\"text-indent:24px\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Arial Unicode MS&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">Groundwater is the word used to describe water that saturates the ground, filling all the available spaces. By far the most abundant type of groundwater is meteoric water; this is the groundwater that circulates as part of the water cycle. Ordinary meteoric water is water that has soaked into the ground from the surface, from precipitation (rain and snow) and from lakes and streams. There it remains, sometimes for long periods, before emerging at the surface again. At first thought it seems incredible that there can be enough space in the “solid” ground underfoot to hold all this water. </span></p><p style=\"text-indent:24px\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Arial Unicode MS&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-indent:24px\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Arial Unicode MS&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">The necessary space is there, however, in many forms. The commonest spaces are those among the particles—sand grains and tiny pebbles—of loose, unconsolidated sand and gravel. Beds of this material, out of sight beneath the soil, are common. They are found wherever fast rivers carrying loads of coarse sediment once flowed. For example, as the great ice sheets that covered North America during the last ice age steadily melted away, huge volumes of water flowed from them. The water was always laden with pebbles, gravel, and sand, known as glacial outwash, that was deposited as the flow slowed down.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br/></p>',1487627077,'js',2,4),(6,'How much has Trump achieved so far?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: left;\">The vice<span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">eaders that, despite Mr Trump&#39;s criticism, the US remains committed to working with Europe.</span></p><p style=\"margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1rem; border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.375; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">-president has been in Brussels for talks with Mr Juncker, Nato Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg, and Donald Tusk, the president of the European Council.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">He has sought to reassure EU l</span>He told leaders it was Mr Trump who told him to visit Brussels and convey the US&#39;s &quot;unwavering&quot; support for Nato.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: left;\">However, he said Nato members had to meet the 2% defence spending target quickly, saying: &quot;America will do our part. But Europe&#39;s defence requires Europe&#39;s commitment as well as ours.&quot;</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: left;\">&quot;The president expects real progress by the end of 2017,&quot; he said, adding that &quot;the patience of the American people will not endure forever&quot;.</p><p><br/></p>',1487627196,'kl',0,5),(7,'Has Mr Pence managed to reassure EU leaders?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><a href=\"http://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2017/02/20-tusk-remarks-meeting-us-vice-president-pence/\" class=\"story-body__link-external\" style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(220, 220, 220); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 1.375; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(17, 103, 168, 0.298039);\">Mr Tusk said</a>&nbsp;his meeting with Mr Pence was &quot;truly needed&quot;, after what he described as &quot;too many new and sometimes surprising opinions&quot; that had been voiced in past months &quot;for us to pretend that everything is as it used to be&quot;.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Mr Tusk said Mr Pence had confirmed the US supported &quot;the idea of a united Europe&quot;.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">EU officials told reporters they were encouraged by the meeting, with one saying &quot;we got everything we were looking for&quot;.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">However, some officials have remarked privately that they will want to hear the same words from Mr Trump before they feel reassured.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Mr Stoltenberg, meanwhile, said he and Mr Pence agreed on the &quot;importance of higher defence spending and fairer burden sharing&quot; in Nato.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&quot;Europeans cannot ask the US to commit to Europe&#39;s defence if they are not willing to commit more themselves.&quot;</p><p><span class=\"image-and-copyright-container\" style=\"border: 0px; color: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; position: relative;\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20170221/1487627230114722.jpg\" class=\"responsive-image__img js-image-replace\" alt=\"Grey line\" width=\"464\" height=\"2\"/></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1rem; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 1.375; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\">Analysis by Damian Grammaticas, BBC Europe correspondent</strong></p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">For European leaders this was reassurance, of a sort.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">When the US vice-president arrived in Europe at the weekend and didn&#39;t mention US backing for the EU it was noted. Now Mr Pence has done so, importantly in the home of the EU&#39;s institutions, standing side by side with Mr Tusk and Mr Juncker.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But the fact Europeans were waiting for a US leader to make such a statement is a sign these are uncertain times. And it leaves a nagging feeling among Europeans that they can&#39;t be sure President Trump will stick to the same script or differ in his next tweet or unscripted remark.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">So for many Europeans the Trump administration remains unpredictable, unclear in its thinking, even divided on key issues.</p><p><br/></p>',1487627231,'dfsd',12,7),(8,'Trump names new national security adviser',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p class=\"story-body__introduction\" style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">More than 100 workers in the US have lost their jobs after taking part in last week&#39;s Day Without Immigrants protest, US media say.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 23px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Dozens of people, including construction workers and restaurant staff, reported being fired after staying at home on Thursday.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The protest aimed to highlight the contribution of immigrants in the US.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">One employer told CNN his staff would have to &quot;pay the price&quot; of standing up for what they believed in.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Jim Serowski, of JVS Masonry in Commerce City, Colorado, said he had no regrets after sacking about 30 bricklayers.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&quot;They were warned, &#39;if you do this you&#39;re hurting the company, and if you go against the team you&#39;re not a member of the team&#39;,&quot;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://edition.cnn.com/2017/02/20/us/workers-fired-day-without-immigrants/\" class=\"story-body__link-external\" style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(220, 220, 220); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 1.375; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(17, 103, 168, 0.298039);\">he was quoted as saying.</a></p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The exact number of workers fired is not clear, however US outlets reported a series of sackings. Among those who said they had lost their jobs were 12 restaurant workers in Tulsa, Oklahoma, who&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.foxnews.com/us/2017/02/20/dozens-workers-lose-their-jobs-for-participating-in-day-without-immigrants-protest.html\" class=\"story-body__link-external\" style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(220, 220, 220); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 1.375; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(17, 103, 168, 0.298039);\">spoke to Fox News&nbsp;</a>and 18 employees at a commercial painting company in Nolensville, Tennessee,<a href=\"http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/employees-across-u-s-fired-after-joining-day-without-immigrants-n722991\" class=\"story-body__link-external\" style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(220, 220, 220); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 1.375; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(17, 103, 168, 0.298039);\">&nbsp;according to NBC</a>.</p><p><br/></p>',1487627290,'dfd',0,1),(9,'Kurt Cobain would have been 50 today: Six reasons why we still love him',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&quot;What&#39;s alternative? What&#39;s counterculture? What&#39;s cool? Who knows? Who cares? If chasing cool is important to you, you&#39;re an idiot!&quot;, Kurt said in&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.livenirvana.com/interviews/9110fa/index.html\" class=\"story-body__link-external\" style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(220, 220, 220); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 1.375; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(17, 103, 168, 0.298039);\">a 1991 interview</a>.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">And, for someone who came to be seen as a spokesperson for his generation, Kurt rejected any hype about their so-called &quot;overnight&quot; success (actually five years in the making).</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&quot;I&#39;m not into ambition or salesmanship, we&#39;re not some new trend. We never meant or tried to be cool, or be a &#39;buzz&#39; band. It never even entered our minds.&quot;</p><p><span class=\"image-and-copyright-container\" style=\"border: 0px; color: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; position: relative;\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20170221/1487627359129172.jpg\" class=\"responsive-image__img js-image-replace\" alt=\"White space\" width=\"1024\" height=\"20\"/></span></p><h2 class=\"story-body__crosshead\" style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(30, 30, 30); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: inherit; line-height: 1.2; margin: 18px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The music he wrote inspired generations</h2><p><span class=\"image-and-copyright-container\" style=\"border: 0px; color: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; position: relative;\"></span></p><p><br/></p>',1487627361,'fsdfs',1,3),(10,'His performances were legendary',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">It would be easier to list who Nirvana didn&#39;t influence than who they did. Lana Del Rey, Blink-182, Justin Timberlake and Jay Z have all quoted Nirvana songs in their own lyrics, while Weezer once played an entire concert of Nirvana covers.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&quot;Cobain changed the course of where the music went,&quot; said Vernon Reid of rock band Living Colour. &quot;There are certain people where you can see the axis of musical history twisting on them: Hendrix was pivotal, Prince was pivotal, Cobain was pivotal.&quot;</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Nirvana launched a million garage bands - the simple barre chords that open Smells Like Teen Spirit are the first song many guitarists learn - and helped foster a do-it-yourself attitude that now permeates everything from indie to pop and grime.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">They introduced legions of fans to alternative music, pushing associated acts like Soundgarden, Pearl Jam and Kurt&#39;s favourites The Pixies into the mainstream.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.livenirvana.com/interviews/9110fa/index.html\" class=\"story-body__link-external\" style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(220, 220, 220); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 1.375; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(17, 103, 168, 0.298039);\">speaking in 1991</a>, Kurt downplayed his own musical talents.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&quot;I don&#39;t understand anything technical about music at all. I don&#39;t understand any of it, why you can&#39;t put these sounds together with those sounds. I only know what sounds good to us.</p><p style=\"border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375; margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&quot;I, or we as a band, never really copied anybody or spent time learning other people&#39;s songs. We were never good enough or had the patience to do it! So we put that energy into putting our own stuff together. We&#39;re from the learn-­as­-you-­play school. We&#39;re still in it.&quot;</p><p><br/></p>',1487627393,'su',2,1);
